cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper proposes a method for compressing deep neural networks, specifically for image classification and semantic segmentation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new type of network layer and uses optimization techniques, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves channel selection and sparsity criteria, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
